The paper discusses the usage of generative models in computer vision and image classification, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also mentions advancements in machine learning, which is a broad category that includes sub-categories such as machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper discusses modifications to the original Generative Adversarial Networks framework, which could fall under the category of graphics (cs.GR).
